The paper discusses the community structure of complex networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with the analysis of social and information networks. cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories as the paper proposes modifications to existing algorithms for community detection. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are less likely but still possible categories as they both deal with the analysis of large-scale networks.
